{"lemma":"طاقَةٌ","slug":"طاقَةٌ","root":"ط.#.ق","root_slug":"ط-_-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-_-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طاقَة","root":"طوق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27324","n27332"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"power, strength; fortitude, endurance","examples":[{"text":"رَبَّنَا وَلَا تُحَمِّلْنَا مَا لَا طَاقَةَ لَنَا بِهِ","english":"Our Lord, and burden us not with that which we have no ability to bear."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"energy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"window"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From طاق (ṭāq, “arch, doorway, opening in a wall”), from Middle Iranian *tāk (“arch”). Ultimately from Proto-Indo-European *teg-, and akin to Latin toga (“garment”) and Ancient Greek στέγος (stégos, “roof”)."},"ipa":["/tˤaː.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27324","headword_ar":"طَاقَهُ","root":"Twq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawoqN","text_ar":"طَوْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27332","headword_ar":"طَاقَةٌ","root":"Twq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is the subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTaAqa","text_ar":"اَطَاقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, Msb, K,) and is used in the place of the inf. n., (Az, TA,) and [when used as a simple subst.] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, * Msb, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawoqN","text_ar":"طَوْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) which is [originally] an inf. n., (Az, K,) and is also expl. as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utmost that one can do, with difficulty, trouble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inconvenience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA TaAqapa liY bihi","text_ar":"لَا طَاقَةَ لِى بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not ability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power, to do it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to bear"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endure"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tolerate it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to cope with him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see Kur ii. last verse: and verse 250:) and] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa fiY TawoqiY","text_ar":"هُوَ فِى طَوْقِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is within my ability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talabotahu TaAqataka","text_ar":"طَلَبْتَهُ طَاقَتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou soughtest him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, in thy state of ability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] Sb says, the [quasi-] inf. n. is prefixed [to the pronoun, and thus rendered determinate], though occupying the place of a denotative of state; in like manner as the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"is prefixed [to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ErAk","text_ar":"عراك"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arosalahaA","text_ar":"اَرْسَلَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slender and small bundle"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fascicle of fibres"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filaments"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, one of those whereof two or more, twisted together, compose a rope; a strand, a yarn, a single twist,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single thread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a rope or cord or fringe &c.] You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqapN mino","text_ar":"طَاقَةٌ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabolK","text_ar":"حَبْلٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A strand, yarn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single twist, of a rope;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quw~apN","text_ar":"قُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quw~apN","text_ar":"قُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino HabolK","text_ar":"مِنْ حَبْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqN","text_ar":"طَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTowaAqN","text_ar":"اَطْوَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (JK voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quw~apN","text_ar":"قُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqapN","text_ar":"طَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqaAtN","text_ar":"طَاقَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqaAtu AlHaboli","text_ar":"طَاقَاتُ الحَبْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwaAhu","text_ar":"قُوَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is said in the A. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEobap","text_ar":"شُعْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spring, spray, bunch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branchlet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of sweet basil, or of sweet-smelling plants: and likewise ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of hair: (JK, TA:) [and so of wool, and the like;] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqapu rayoHaAnK","text_ar":"طَاقَةُ رَيْحَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, TA,) [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino rayoHaAnK","text_ar":"مِنْ رَيْحَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEobapN minohu","text_ar":"شُعْبَةٌ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the A. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqapu naEolK","text_ar":"طَاقَةُ نَعْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqN","text_ar":"طَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half. ―         -b4-  See also another meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqapN","text_ar":"طَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAqN","text_ar":"طَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first quarter."}],"source_refs":["Az","Msb","K","TA","S","O","JK"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}